Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, quickly
brown off the @British beef mince{500%g}, then remove from the frying pan and keep
to the side.

Peel and chop the @onions{2} in half lengthways through the root, then very thinly
slice them widthways into half moon shapes. Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} on medium-low
heat in your (now empty) frying pan and cook the onions for around ~{6%minutes},
then add the @Mexican spice{2}.

> Use more or less spice depending on how hot you like it!

Whilst the onion cooks, drain and thoroughly rinse your @red kidney beans{1%tin}.
Mash up the kidney beans in a #bowl{}.

Once the onion has softened, stir in the mashed beans. Add the beef mince back
into the frying pan. Stir in the @tomato passata{2} with @salt{1/2%tsp} then
refill the carton a fifth with water, swirl it around and add this too.

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Let the mixture bubble away gently on low
heat until it has thickened enough to fill your tortillas. Meanwhile roughly
chop the @baby gem lettuce{2} and roughly chop the @vine tomatoes{4}.

Once the sauce is thick, take it off the heat. Divide the mixture into eight
equal portions and spoon it along one end of each @super soft tortillas with
whole wheat{8}. Roll up the tortillas, place in a #baking dish{} and grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{8%g} over the top. Cook in the oven until the cheese melts.

Whilst your enchiladas are in the oven, zest your @lime{1}. Mix the
@sour cream{2} with a few good grinds of @black pepper{} and the lime zest.

Toss the tomatoes and baby gem lettuce in @olive oil{2%tbsp}, your lime juice
and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Serve your enchiladas with a dollop of
sour cream and the salad on the side. Devour immediately!